abstract: You used to need a secret recording to learn what politicians said in private. Now we can get the same illicit thrill from their public statements.
snippet: You used to need a secret recording to learn what politicians said in private. Now we can get the same illicit thrill from their public statements.
lead_paragraph: Joe Biden is suited, floating in a black void of stage, sitting cross-legged across from a glamorous woman in a striking red jacket, speaking to an invisible crowd. “The younger generation now tells me how tough things are,” he says. “Give me a break. No, no, I have no empathy for it. Give me a break. Because here’s the deal, guys: We decided we were going to change the world. And we did.” He delivers the line in high avuncular style, stating an opinion with the tone and cadence of a meaningful story. The crowd, whoever they are, laughs. They’re not the “guys” being told what the “deal” is. Those people are somewhere else.
